                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>This MS., also given to me at Constantinople in April, 1908, by Dr Ridá
                                Tawfiq, comprises 165 ff. of 16.4 x 10.5 cm and 12-16 ll., is written in
                                different Turkish naskh hands, all legible, and is dated in the colophon on
                                f. 165b Shawwal 29, 1193/Nov. 9, 1779. It contains the five following
                                tracts:</p>
                            <p>(1) Questions put to Mullá Sa'íd by a dervish in 994/1586 as to the reasons
                                for various regulations as to the performance of prayers, etc., with the
                                answers in Turkish (ff. 4-16). Dated Muharram, 1192/Feb. 1778.</p>
                            <p>(2) The Akhbár-náma of Firishta-oghlu (ff. 17-72), in Turkish prose, dated
                                the beginning of Dhu'l-Qa'da, 1191/Dec. 22, 1776. I have two other MSS. of
                                this work (E. 4 and E. 13), and there is another in the British Museum
                                (Or. 5961).</p>
                            <p>(3) A Turkish mathnawí poem by "Lá Makání" (ff. 74-97), beginning:</p>
                            <p>(4) Another Turkish prose treatise (ff. 98-128b) entitled Kitáb-i-Mawlá
                                Iláhí, beginning:</p>
                            <p>کف و دود سیاهی علم ایلر زمی صانع خه ماهی آدم ایلر</p>
                            <p>حمد جمیل بی حد و شکر جزیل بی عد اول خالق كولين و رزاق الثقلين الخ</p>
                            <p>Copied in Jumádà I, 1182/Sept.-Oct., 1768.</p>
                            <p>(5) Another Turkish prose treatise entitled Tuhfatu'l-'Ushsháq (ff. 129-165)
                                beginning, after the very incorrect Arabic doxology:</p>
                            <p>اما بعده بلکل و آگاه اولغيل كى حق سبحانه و تعالی کلام قدیمنده بيورر وما خلقت
                                الجن و الانس الا لیعبدون اى ليعرفون ای لیوحدون دیرلر یعنی بیورر جبله انسی
                                براتمدم الا بكا عبادت الملجون براندم ظاهرا معناسی بودر كي ويدك الخ</p>
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="E_8-item1">
                            <locus from="4" to="16">ff. 4-16</locus>
                            <title xml:lang="en" type="desc">Questions put to Mullá Sa'íd by a
                                dervish (994/1586) on the reasons for various regulations
                                concerning prayer, with answers in Turkish</title>
                            <note>The present copy is dated Muḥarram, 1192/Feb. 1778.</note>
                            <incipit/>
                            <explicit/>
                            <textLang mainLang="ota">Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
                        </msItem>
